  "local_port": 49250,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I change One Plus 3 ringtone?",
  "response": "Changing the ringtone on your OnePlus 3 is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. **Unlock your phone**: Make sure your OnePlus 3 is turned on and unlocked.\n\n2. **Open Settings**: From the home screen, swipe down from the top of the screen to open the notification shade. Then, tap on the gear icon at the top to open the Settings menu.\n\n3. **Sound & notification**: In the Settings menu, scroll down and tap on \"Sound & notification.\"\n\n4. **Phone Ringtone**: In the Sound & notification menu, look for and tap on \u201cPhone ringtone.\u201d\n\n5. **Select a ringtone**: You will see a list of available ringtones. Tap on any ringtone to preview it. When you find one you like, select it.\n\n6. **Set the ringtone**: After selecting your desired ringtone, tap \u201cOK\u201d or \u201cApply\u201d (depending on your phone's interface) to confirm your choice.\n\nIf you want to use a custom ringtone (such as a song or a sound file you have), here\u2019s what you need to do:\n\n1. **Move the file**: Ensure the sound file you want to use is saved on your phone. It should be in a recognized format like MP3.\n\n2. **Open File Manager**: Use the File Manager app to locate the sound file.\n\n3. **Move to ringtones folder**: If the file isn't already in the \"Ringtones\" folder, move or copy it there. This folder is typically located in Internal Storage.\n\n4. **Repeat steps 2-4 from above**: Go back to Settings > Sound & notification > Phone ringtone. You should now see your custom ringtone listed among the default ones.\n\n5. **Select your custom ringtone**: Tap on your custom ringtone from the list to select it, and press OK or Apply.\n\nThat\u2019s it! Your OnePlus 3 should now ring with your chosen ringtone.",
